sub_title: Researcher Resilience Management & Governance @ KWR Water Research Institute
summary: Noor is a researcher in the field of resilience management and governance. She focuses on customer behaviour, environmental management and water in the circular economy. In this, she actively interacts with drinking water companies and also works in large European consortia. In her thesis at KWR, she applied the City Blueprint Approach to identify city-to-city learning lessons for Uzbek cities. Based on 26 interviews with stakeholder organisations and working closely with UNESCO, Noor conducted an in-depth analysis of the administrative problem-solving capacity of Tashkent, the capital of Uzbekistan, to provide access to water services to its population.
